cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.CR 

This paper analyzes the effect of sponsored data platforms in the context of competition between ISPs and content providers. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses game theory and optimization techniques to model the decision-making of the different players, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses pricing dynamics and market structure, which could place it in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
